Alitalia SpA expects to report a
full-year 2010 loss and break even at the operating level in
2011, Chief Executive Officer Rocco Sabelli told Il Sole 24 Ore
in an interview.  The airline forecasts a loss of about 30 million euros ($42
million) in the fourth quarter, the CEO told the financial
newspaper. Alitalia has signed an agreement with Germanyâ€™s
Deutsche Bahn AG to offer air and rail travel packages, Il Sole
